[{"short_id":"ibfmsg","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ibfmsg","created_at":"2025-03-05T16:06:42.000-06:00","title":"The Hitchhiker's Guide to Digital Colour","url":"https://hg2dc.com/","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/ibfmsg/hitchhiker_s_guide_digital_colour","submitter_user":"YogurtGuy","user_is_author":false,"tags":["art","cogsci","graphics"]},{"short_id":"itcqle","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/itcqle","created_at":"2025-03-05T15:46:35.000-06:00","title":"A good memory allocator in 200 lines of code","url":"https://github.com/ziglang/zig/blob/0.14.0/lib/std/heap/SmpAllocator.zig","score":5,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"\u003cp\u003eHi Lobsters,\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI know people here may be tired of seeing too many Zig stories, but, I think this is a legitimately cool discovery that transcends programming language turf wars.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis is a memory allocator that \u003ca href=\"https://ziglang.org/devlog/2025/#2025-02-07\" rel=\"ugc\"\u003eoutcompetes glibc malloc\u003c/a\u003e with an incredibly simple implementation, that can be read and understood in a matter of minutes, even if you have never used the programming language it is written in, even if this is your first time considering a memory allocator implementation.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI am the author of this code, which is fairly new and not yet battle-tested. Maybe I’m missing something crucial, or maybe it’s going to become a specimen for computer science students to learn about memory allocation from. Either way, I hope you will find it interesting and on-topic here.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI added the “zig” tag out of courtesy, but it’s really not the point of the story, the point is that it’s possible to implement a good memory allocator that is also conceptually simple.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e-Andrew\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Hi Lobsters,\r\n\r\nI know people here may be tired of seeing too many Zig stories, but, I think this is a legitimately cool discovery that transcends programming language turf wars.\r\n\r\nThis is a memory allocator that [outcompetes glibc malloc](https://ziglang.org/devlog/2025/#2025-02-07) with an incredibly simple implementation, that can be read and understood in a matter of minutes, even if you have never used the programming language it is written in, even if this is your first time considering a memory allocator implementation.\r\n\r\nI am the author of this code, which is fairly new and not yet battle-tested. Maybe I'm missing something crucial, or maybe it's going to become a specimen for computer science students to learn about memory allocation from. Either way, I hope you will find it interesting and on-topic here.\r\n\r\nI added the \"zig\" tag out of courtesy, but it's really not the point of the story, the point is that it's possible to implement a good memory allocator that is also conceptually simple.\r\n\r\n-Andrew","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/itcqle/good_memory_allocator_200_lines_code","submitter_user":"andrewrk","user_is_author":true,"tags":["programming","zig"]},{"short_id":"fyxiao","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fyxiao","created_at":"2025-03-05T14:33:03.000-06:00","title":"Pokemon Red (Reinforcement Learning Edition)","url":"https://drubinstein.github.io/pokerl/","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/fyxiao/pokemon_red_reinforcement_learning","submitter_user":"ema-pe","user_is_author":false,"tags":["ai"]},{"short_id":"oegolv","short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oegolv","created_at":"2025-03-05T14:19:48.000-06:00","title":"Git without a forge","url":"https://www.chiark.greenend.org.uk/~sgtatham/quasiblog/git-no-forge/","score":15,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"","description_plain":"","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/oegolv/git_without_forge","submitter_user":